dialogue.introduction: Good morning! I'm the heavy cruiser Prinz Eugen. Nice to meet you!
dialogue.library_intro: Oh! You surprised me! I, German-born heavy cruiser, Prinz Eugen! Admiral Hipper class, third ship. With big sister Bismarck, I took part in Operation Rhein√ºbung. Lucky fleet ... really? I will keep fighting in this sea too!
dialogue.secretary1: Oh! You surprised me! ..Ah, yes! Setting off!
dialogue.secretary3: Admiraal! Is it the Rhine Exercise? ...Ah.. So I was mistaken.. It's okay! I'll still work hard! Leave it to me!
dialogue.secretaryidle: Bismarck Nee-sama... I wonder if she's okay...? I'm kind of curious... Maybe I should go see what she's doing?
dialogue.secretarymarried: Fuwaa, Admiral-san, if you're tired, you need to take a break. Definitely! Got it!?
dialogue.wedding: Admiral-san, you said you needed something? Wah, t-this is for me? Uh, umm~, Bismarck Nee-sama is... a-ah... u-um, ...Thank you! I'll treasure it!!
dialogue.show_players_score: Information about the fleet, right~? Wait a minute~ Ho~, ho~oho~ I seee~
dialogue.joining_a_fleet: Heavy Cruiser Prinz Eugen, setting off!
dialogue.docking_minor_damage: Haa... I got hit. I'll get fixed soon
dialogue.docking_complete: Ship in dock is fully repaired!
dialogue.ship_construction: It looks like new ships have been commissioned. Looking forward to it!
dialogue.return_from_sortie: Operation complete! Thank you for the hard work~
dialogue.start_a_sortie: Bismarck Nee-sama, let's head out together!
dialogue.night_attack: Main guns... carefully aim... firing, commence!
dialogue.artillery_spotting: Main guns... carefully aim... firing, commence!
dialogue.night_special_attack_modifier_cutin_at_n: Main guns... carefully aim... firing, commence!
dialogue.support_expedition_team_arrival: Main guns... carefully aim... firing, commence!
dialogue.mvp: Ehh, I'm a lucky girl? Nothing of that sort! I'm bad at stuff like the shallows, after all...
dialogue.minor_damaged1: Uwaa I got hit! But, I'm not done yet..!
dialogue.minor_damaged2: Uu...I need to snap out of it...
dialogue.moderately_damaged: I'll get laughed at by Bismarck Nee-sama like this..!
dialogue.sunk: This time I'll go on ahead... Sakawa... Nagato... See you...
dialogue.christmas_2014: As I thought, Christmas is all about enjoying Stollen and Lebkuchen! They're tasty, aren't they~?
dialogue.new_year_2015: This is a Japanese new year. There are "2 Priests"...! Kadoma-2, too, is unique and wonderful...!
dialogue.second_anniversary_2015: Today is a wonderful day! Good work as usual, Admiral-san! Ehehe
dialogue.setsubun_2016: So this is Japan's culture, Setsubun! I throw this bean at Nagato, right? Hyah! Oh?!

hourly.0000: Uwaa!? It's exactly 0 o'clock! Today, it's this Prinz Eugen's duty to tell you the time. Alright, I got it! Leave it to me!
hourly.0100: It's 1am! Is something like this good? Ah, I see! Thank goodness!
hourly.0200: It's 2am. In this country, you say... Ushi, Mitsu, Doki? Aah, they are funny sounding words.
hourly.0300: Waa, you startled me! Ah, do you like... this hairstyle? Aah! It's 3am!
hourly.0400: Nnn~... It's 4am~... nn... As expected, I'm a bit tired... But, I'm fine.
hourly.0500: It's 5 o'clock! Guten Morgen, it's a nice morning! Let's do our best!
hourly.0600: 6 o'clock. Breakfast, huh... eh? Me!? Got it, leave it to me! Umm... hmm, what should I make? I wonder if I should make Bismarck Nee-sama's portion too? Right?
hourly.0700: Ok, today's breakfast is bread, cheese, and sausage. Also salad... and of course, have some hot coffee! It's pretty average, but still good, right? Ah, it's exactly 7 o'clock now.
hourly.0800: It's now 8 o'clock. Now, Admiral-san, let's do today's missions! Will you start with exercises? Or maybe, expeditions?
hourly.0900: It's 9am. Hm? Ah, it's Nagato! Ooy, Na-gato! ...hm? Where have we met? That is, of course! ...uh... huh? Umm... where was it...?
hourly.1000: It's 10 o'clock. Battleship? 'Course! If I'm with Bismarck Nee-sama, we'll sink them in no time! Leave it to me!
hourly.1100: It's now 11am~. It's almost noon, huh~. It might be nice to eat outside today.
hourly.1200: Ah, it's already noon! It's midday! For lunch, is cheese and bread outside ok? Since it's nice, shall we have a beer too? Aha, no good, huh...
hourly.1300: It's now 13 o'clock. Time to start the afternoon missions. Let's do our best!
hourly.1400: 14 o'clock. Eh? What, Sakawa? Ah, I know her, she's that cute light cruiser.
hourly.1500: 15 o'clock. Aah, this? It's my fittings from Operation Cerberus. How is it, does it suit me~?
hourly.1600: It's now 16 o'clock. Waa, you startled me, Bismarck Nee-sama! Shall we sortie together? Yes, by all means.
hourly.1700: 17 o'clock. It's evening now. It's about time for the day to be getting darker. Haa, such a beautiful sky... Ah, of course Bismarck Nee-sama is the most beautiful!
hourly.1800: It's 18 o'clock. I'll start preparing dinner. Is kaltes essen ok for today? Eh, it's not? Something warm would be better?
hourly.1900: It's 19 o'clock. Well then, dinner is Eisbein pot-au-feu. It's fine if the flavor soaks into the soup, right? And finally, if you add in rice to make it a porridge, it's delicious!
hourly.2000: It's now 20 o'clock. Japanese cruisers are pretty well-rounded, huh? Mmhmm. Aah, I see... Mmhmm.
hourly.2100: 21 o'clock. Eh, a... signature move? Let's see, I spent a lot of time shelling hordes of advancing enemy tanks! I'm pretty good at that! Yes!
hourly.2200: 22 o'clock, it's completely nighttime now. Admiral-san, good work on today's operations too.
hourly.2300: It's 23 o'clock. Hm~ it's about time I took a break too... Gute Nacht... Eh, I can't~?
